272
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:32,320
We talked about product for a little bit. 
I want to spend a little time on product  

273
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:37,080
management. I'm curious just how you think about 
product management. There's this constant debate  

274
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:41,440
across tech companies about the value of PMs. 
Are we better with more PMs? Are there too many  

275
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:46,880
PMs? What do PMs do for you? You're a chief 
product officer. Where do you find product  

276
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:51,000
managers bring the most value to Canva? 
And then do you just have thought on the  

277
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:56,080
future of the field of product management?
I don't know. It's one of those things that I  

278
00:24:56,080 --> 00:25:04,400
don't want to quantify. I don't want to put it in 
a box and say this is product management. Because  

279
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:10,320
I've worked at a few places now. I've actually 
only had one real job, which was at Google where  

280
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:15,760
I got to experience product managers the Google 
way. And the way that they do product management  

