297
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:53,080
exactly what we wanted and how we built product 
and how to communicate that to someone else  

298
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:58,240
and get them to do it in a similar way and 
work with the teams in the way that we did.
 

299
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:09,160
For us, product managers are really connectives. 
They connect the team, ideas, data, a whole bunch  

300
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:16,560
of different things, and it's very messy. There's 
no exact recipe for how to do it, but connecting  

301
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:25,320
these disparate areas and moving the team and 
the technology and our customers to a new place,  

302
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:30,840
a new vision is essentially what product managers 
do, and it's going to involve compromise,  

303
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:36,680
it's going to involve changes in the feature 
scope, it's going to involve timelines of like,  

304
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:40,320
"Okay, we can't ship it in May, it's going 
to have to be July. Let's figure out what we  

305
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:48,120
can do with marketing to make that work." This 
constant movement and connection and reorienting  

306
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:53,600
around the constraints that have suddenly 
arisen in the last week, and that's where we  

307
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:59,360
see great product managers operating in Canva.
You mentioned Mel and Cliff. For folks that don't  

308
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:04,200
know, they're the other two co-founders of Canva 
and they were dating when they were starting  

309
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:09,560
Canva, I think it was called Fusion Books back 
in the day before Canva. Now, they're married.  

310
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:14,520
What's it like working with a married couple as 
the other two co-founders, and is there something  

311
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:22,200
they did well that didn't make you feel like this 
third wheel person that isn't married to them?
 

312
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:28,840
It is always tricky working with a couple because 
they're on it 24/7. When you leave the office and  

313
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:35,040
they head home, they're still talking about 
product, business strategy, all the things. I  

